reviewText: not what expected, not naughty enough

I just saw this from beginning to end, and it was a lot of fun.  Well made, funny and had a human side, also a moral side.  Instead of just showing T and A on girls, which it did, it had the main character girls be a bit likable for the girls in the audience to have something to watch too.  And it seemed to have a conscience, the film, and overall just entertaining, with a happy ending and nice end credit sequence to leave you in a good mood.

This one is a weird flick... even for the troma addicts. The image suffers from a lack of care, and the whole film looks like it's been shot in 3 days. It's a shame considering that the subject is so crazy that it could have been a lot more challenging than a poor quality DV film.
Give it a chance though, it might as well make you laugh.
